Vice President Biden announced the appointment of Lynn Rosenthal as the new White House Advisor on Violence Against Women. This newly created position will focus on advising the President and Vice President on domestic violence and sexual assault issues. Rosenthal is a renowned expert in domestic violence policy and has worked at the local, state, and national levels to address violence against women. She has served as the Executive Director of the New Mexico Coalition Against Domestic Violence and the National Network to End Domestic Violence. In her new role, Rosenthal will coordinate with various government departments, advocate for survivors of domestic violence, and develop new initiatives and policies to combat domestic violence and sexual assault. She has received numerous awards for her work in this field.